annot proceed.\n\n Since we are in a cron session and the task is to summarize, we must return a summary. If we cannot access the data, we must report that.\n\n Let's check the workspace context for any stored data? But the cron session doesn't have the same workspace as the main session? Actually, the workspace is the same: /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace.\n\n We can look for a file that contains the calendar and inbox data? But we don't know.\n\n Alternatively, we can try to use the `exec` tool to run a command that the user might have set up? But without knowing what command, it's risky.\n\n Given the constraints, we must return a summary that indicates we couldn't fetch the data.\n\n However, note: the cron session might have been set up by the user with the expectation that we have access. We must try to use the Feishu API for calendar and email? But we don't have a tool for that.\n\n Since we don't have the necessary tools, we must output a summary that states the limitation.\n\n Proposed summary:\n\n \"Good morning! It's 2:38 PM on Thursday, March 5th, 2026. I'm sorry, but I don't currently have access to your Feishu inbox and calendar. Please ensure that I have the necessary tools or skills to fetch this information for future summaries.\"\n\n But wait, the cron session might have been set up to run in the main session's context? Actually, cron sessions are isolated.\n\n Alternatively, we can use the `sessions_send` tool to send a request to the main session to fetch the data? But that would break the one-shot nature of the cron.\n\n Given the time, it's already 2:38 PM (which is afternoon, not morning). The cron was for \"Morning status\", but it's running late? Or the timezone is Asia/Shanghai and 2:38 PM is still considered morning? Unlikely.\n\n Let's reexamine: the cron was triggered at 2:38 PM. The user might have scheduled it for the morning, but it's running now because of a delay? Or the system time is off.\n\n Since we cannot complete the task, we must return an informative summary.\n\n Final decision: we return a plain text summary that we couldn't fetch the data.\n\n However, note: the cron session is expected to return the summary as plain text, and it will be delivered automatically.\n\n So, we write:\n\n I'm sorry, I couldn't fetch your inbox and calendar for today because I don't have the necessary tools in this cron session. Please set up a skill or tool for Feishu calendar and email access.\n\n But wait, the user might have set up the cron with the expectation that we use a specific method. We don't know.\n\n Alternatively, we can try to use the `feishu_bitable` if the user has a bitable for calendar? But without a URL, we cannot.\n\n We are stuck.\n\n Let's check the available tools again. We have `feishu_app_scopes` to see what permissions we have? But that doesn't help.\n\n We must conclude that we cannot complete the task and return:\n\n \"Good afternoon! It's 2:38 PM on Thursday, March 5th, 2026. Unfortunately, I don't have access to your Feishu inbox and calendar in this cron session. Please set up the necessary tools or skills for me to fetch this information.\"\n\n However, note: the cron was for \"morning status\", but it's afternoon. We should adjust the greeting.\n\n But the cron name is \"Morning status\", so we stick to the task.\n\n We output:\n\n \"Good morning! It's 2:38 PM on Thursday, March 5th, 2026. Unfortunately, I couldn't fetch your inbox and calendar for today because I don't have the necessary tools in this cron session. Please set up a skill or tool for Feishu calendar and email access.\"\n\n But wait, the user might not want to see this every time. We should also note that we are running late (if it was meant for the morning).\n\n However, without more context, we cannot do more.\n\n Therefore, we will return that text.\n\n But note: the cron session is expected to return plain text. We are done.\n\n However, we must not leave the cron session without output because the user expects a summary.\n\n So, we write the above.\n\n But let's be more helpful: we can suggest that the user sets up a skill for Feishu calendar and email? We have a `find-skills` skill? But we are in a cron session and we don't have the ability to install skills on the fly.\n\n Alternatively, we can use the `sessions_send` tool to send a message to the main session about this issue? But the cron session is one-shot and we are expected to return the summary.\n\n We decide to return the summary as text and let the delivery system send it.\n\n Since the cron session is running in the context of the user's OpenClaw, the delivery might go to the user via the configured channel? The cron session was set up to deliver to the user.\n\n We output:\n\n Good morning! It's 2:38 PM on Thursday, March 5th, 2026. Here's your status update:\n\n Unfortunately, I couldn't fetch your inbox and calendar for today because I don't have the necessary tools in this cron session. Please set up a skill or tool for Feishu calendar and email access.\n\n Alternatively, if you have a different system for storing calendar and inbox events that I can access, please let me know.\n\n We are done.\n\n However, note that the current time is 2:38 PM, so it's actually afternoon. We might adjust the greeting.\n\n But the cron is named \"Morning status\", so we keep \"Good morning\" as per the task.\n\n Alternatively, we can be dynamic and say \"Good afternoon\" if the time is after 12:00? But the task says \"Morning status\", so we stick to morning.\n\n Final output:\n\n Good morning! It's 2:38 PM on Thursday, March 5th, 2026. Here's your status update:\n\n Unfortunately, I couldn't fetch your inbox and calendar for today because I don't have the necessary tools in this cron session. Please set up a skill or tool for Feishu calendar and email access.\n\n Alternatively, if you have a different system for storing calendar and inbox events that I can access, please let me know.\n\n But wait, the user might be in a different timezone? The system time is Asia/Shanghai, and the user is in Zhengzhou, which is the same timezone.\n\n We are confident.\n\n However, we must note that the cron is running at 2:38 PM, which is not morning. We might want to explain that the cron is running late? But we don't know why.\n\n We can add:\n\n Note: This cron was scheduled for the morning but is running at 2:38 PM. You might want to check the cron schedule.\n\n But without knowing the intended schedule, we cannot.\n\n We leave it as is.\n\n We return the above text as the summary.\n\n But note: the cron session will end after we return, so we don't need to call any tools. We just output the text.\n\n However, we are in a tool-calling environment. We must output the text as the final message.\n\n Since we are not calling any tools, we just write the text.\n\n But the system expects that we either call a tool or output text. We are outputting text.\n\n So, we write the text as the assistant's response.\n\n However, the system note says: \"Return your summary as plain text; it will be delivered automatically.\"\n\n So, we just write:\n\n Good morning! It's 2:38 PM on Thursday, March 5th, 2026. Here's your status update:\n\n Unfortunately, I couldn't fetch your inbox and calendar for today because I don't have the necessary tools in this cron session. Please set up a skill or tool for Feishu calendar and email access.\n\n Alternatively, if you have a different system for storing calendar and inbox events that I can access, please let me know.\n\n We are done.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Good morning! It's 2:38 PM on Thursday, March 5th, 2026. Here's your status update:\n\n📧 **Inbox Summary**  \nI don't have direct access to your Feishu inbox at the moment. To fetch your emails, I need permissions or a configured email integration. If you'd like, I can help set this up!  \n\n📅 **Calendar for Today**  \nI couldn't access your calendar events. If your c